gov.usgs.anss.edge

Class RunListTree

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.edge.RunListTree

  • public final class RunListTree
extends java.lang.Object
    This class keeps a series of runs which may be from different seednames. The starting and ending point of each run is kept. The idea is to simply add data to this class which will add the data to a run if it fits, or create new runs. After all of the runs have been created, the consolidate() method will attempt to eliminate overlapping or adjoining runs into single runs. This uses the RunList to contain runs from a single channels and adds a TreeMap of these RunLists with the channel name is the key. This results in a performance improvement when there are a lot of runs. The original method had to check each possible run to add data where this one pays the TreeMap lookup expense but then only has to check runs for this channel.
